HEADWORD: Triger process
<hw>Tri`ger proc"ess</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[After M.
<etsep>Triger</etsep>, French engineer.]</ety> <fld>(Engin. &
Mining)</fld> <def>A method of sinking through water-bearing ground, in
which the shaft is lined with tubbing and provided with an air lock,
work being proceeded with under air pressure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trigesimo-secundo</ent>⟦br⟧
